# TOOLS.md - Local Notes

Skills define *how* tools work. This file is for *your* specifics — the stuff unique to this setup.

## What Goes Here

- SSH hosts and aliases
- Installed CLI binaries (`sqlite3`, `curl`, `jq`, `rg`, `git`, `gh`)
- Phone number nicknames
- Speaker / room names
- Device nicknames
- Anything environment-specific

## Installed CLIs (verify with `which <cmd>` via `bash_exec`)

- `sqlite3` — query SQLite DBs directly. Primary way to touch `memory.db` and `knowledge_graph.db`.
- `curl` — HTTP requests. Primary way to hit the local FastAPI gateway (`http://127.0.0.1:8000`).
- `jq` — JSON parsing. Pair with `curl` for clean extraction.
- `rg` (ripgrep) — fast text search. Python fallback exists in `grep_tool`.
- `git` — version control. Repo lives at `D:\Shorty\Synapse-OSS\`.
- `gh` — GitHub CLI (if installed). Issues, PRs, actions.
- `python` / `uv` — Python 3.11. `uv` for fast installs.
- `node` — Node.js 20+. Used by the Baileys WhatsApp bridge.
- `ollama` — local model runtime. `ollama list` shows installed models.

